<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="1027" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1027">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0031 Tibet/5–349: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-03T19:00:00-04:00">May 3, 1949—7
                                p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>328. NY FR<note n="10" xml:id="d1027fn10">Federal Reserve.</note> Bank has
                        recd request Leader, Tibet Trade Mission to sell some $US 400,000 of gold
                        for air shipment vaults Hong Kong [and] Shanghai Banking Corp., 31 Dalhousie
                        Square, Calcutta, West Bengal. When Trade Mission in US this Govt inclined
                        to honor such request to Tibetan <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Govt but
                        had misgivings re end use of gold, that is in event premium sales Tibet or
                        elsewhere involved. Pls ascertain discreetly possible end uses and attitude
                        of GoI auths such transaction if approved here. Leader TTM states some dols
                        to be released by GoI.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>